item.description:
@Anfernio wrote:

[quote=“The Soul, post:2, topic:276493”][quote author=Anfernio link=topic=365124.msg2769869#msg2769869 date=1241048537]
I recently added… public void welcome(int recoveryChange, boolean memberWarning, //Made by Anfernio. (Ripped out of Loginhandler. ^.^) int messages, int lastLoginIP, int lastLogin) { outStream.createFrame(176); //Days since last recovery changed to 200 for not set, 201 for Members. //Otherwise, it sends how long ago recoveries were set/changed. outStream.writeByteC(recoveryChange); outStream.writeWordA(messages); // Number of unread messages. outStream.writeByte(memberWarning ? 1 : 0); //1 for if it's members world. //Non-members world waring. outStream.writeDWord_v2(lastLoginIP); //Shows IP of last login. outStream.writeWord(lastLogin); //Days that you last logged in on. } and (If you don’t know what this is, it’s when RS had good login screen.) it sends this error when I add welcome(); to Login.

client.java:9993: welcome(int,boolean,int,int,int) in client cannot be applied t o () welcome(); ^ 1 error Press any key to continue . . is the error. This is my first time ever with this error, so I’d like to know what it means and how I can fix it.
[/quote]

It’s because the method requires the values of the integers ‘recoveryChange’, ‘messages’, ‘lastLoginIP’ and ‘lastLogin’, and if the ‘memberWarning’ boolean is true or false.[/quote]
Reword that for me, please.
